{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc06c7f60-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18795b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"18795b"},"text":"§ 18795b.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" State-based home energy efficiency contractor training grants","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc06c7f61-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18795b/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Appropriation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In addition to amounts otherwise available, there is appropriated to the Secretary for fiscal year 2022, out of any money in the Treasury not otherwise appropriated, $200,000,000, to remain available through ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2031-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 2031","children":[],"tail":", to carry out a program to provide financial assistance to States to develop and implement a State program described in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6322/d/13"},"text":"section 6322(d)(13) of this title","children":[],"tail":", which shall provide training and education to contractors involved in the installation of home energy efficiency and electrification improvements, including improvements eligible for rebates under a HOMES rebate program (as defined in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s18795/d"},"text":"section 18795(d) of this title","children":[],"tail":") or a high-efficiency electric home rebate program (as defined in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s18795a/d"},"text":"section 18795a(d) of this title","children":[],"tail":"), as part of an approved State energy conservation plan under the State Energy Program."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc06c7f62-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18795b/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Use of funds","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"A State may use amounts received under subsection (a)—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc06c7f63-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18795b/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to reduce the cost of training contractor employees;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc06c7f64-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18795b/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to provide testing and certification of contractors trained and educated under a State program developed and implemented pursuant to subsection (a); and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc06c7f65-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18795b/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to partner with nonprofit organizations to develop and implement a State program pursuant to subsection (a).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc06c7f66-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18795b/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Administrative expenses","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Of the amounts received by a State under subsection (a), a State shall use not more than 10 percent for administrative expenses associated with developing and implementing a State program pursuant to that subsection.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc06c7f67-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/169/tV/s50123"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–169, title V, § 50123","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-08-16"},"text":"Aug. 16, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/2041"},"text":"136 Stat. 2041","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idc06c7f68-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idc06c7f69-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idc06c7f6a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/169"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–169","children":[],"tail":", and not as part of div. D of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/58"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–58","children":[],"tail":", which enacted this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idc06c7f6b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"definitions","id":"idc06c7f6c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Definitions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For definitions of “Secretary”, “State”, and “State Energy Program” as used in this section, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/169/s50111"},"text":"section 50111 of Pub. L. 117–169","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s17113b"},"text":"section 17113b of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
